1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 37-01-48 of the North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to the payment of a death benefit to the beneficiary or next of kin of a member of the
3 national guard who died while serving on state active duty; and to declare an emergency.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 37-01-48 of the North Dakota Century Code is
6 amended and reenacted as follows:
7 37-01-48. Payment of death benefits.
8 The national guard may pay a death benefit to a designated beneficiary, or to the next of
9 kin, of a national guard service member who died while serving in a state active duty status
10 under this chapter. The payment of a death benefit may not exceed fifteen thousandone
11 hundred thousand dollars and is subject to available funds. The adjutant general may adopt
12 rules to implement this section.
13 SECTION 2. EMERGENCY. This Act is declared to be an emergency measure.
